 M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/chrome/trunk/src/native_client/src/trusted/plugin/ppapi/plugin_ppapi.h?r1=4305&amp;r2=4304&amp;pathrev=4305

A hack to force Chrome to enable compositing.

Currently, there is a restriction in Chrome that a plugin must create and bind a 3D surface in DidChangeView. nexes are not even loaded by then. We hack around by creating and binding a dummy context in DidChangeView, and then destroy it afterwards.

BUG=910
TEST=chrome actually draws a triangle in hello_triangle gl example

